Unilever Adopts Door-to-Door Sales Method in Africa, FT Says

-- B y   S a r a h   H a l l s
-- 
2011-08-31T00:14:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/unilever-adopts-door-to-door-sales-method-in-africa-ft-says.html
Unilever, the world’s second-biggest
consumer-goods company, will implement its “Shakti” direct-to-
consumers-distribution program in Nigeria and  Kenya , the
Financial Times reported, citing Frank Braeken, executive vice-
president of Unilever’s North Africa,  Middle East  and Central
Africa division.  The program started in  India  and serves more than 3 million
households.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah Halls in London at 
 shalls@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  